title: 820-01987  dropped.   Switches to 19v but pulls little current
message:
The SOC U3900 is the only thing running.   Soft glow in thermal.

L7690 3.3v is stable
L7670 5v comes on for a few seconds then fades away.  Repeats.
L7030 12v comes on for a split second then fades away.  Repeats.

None of the other rails appear to come up.
No rails shorts found.

What is SOC "system on a chip" I assume.    what does it do?

title: 820-01987  dropped.   Switches to 19v but pulls little current
message:
SOC is the T2 chip in this case.

There are other G3S voltages; check if all come on at same time with 5V_G3S.
There should be some broken trace, or solders; maybe under BGA chips.

Did you test if enters DFU mode?
